      <definition value="Design-time archetype identifier of this node taken from its generating archetype; used to build archetype paths. Always in the form of an at-code, e.g.  `at0005`. This value enables a 'standardised' name for this node to be generated, by referring to the generating archetype local terminology. &#xA;&#xA;At an archetype root point, the value of this attribute is always the stringified form of the `_archetype_id_` found in the `_archetype_details_` object."/>
      <min value="1"/>
      <max value="1"/>
      <base>
